they were defeated by Viola's
Surskit and Vivillon.

00:00:19.853 --> 00:00:22.923
Now, following a healing
visit to the Pokémon Center

00:00:22.923 --> 00:00:25.359
Ash has begun preparing
for a rematch

00:00:25.359 --> 00:00:27.427
with training assistance
provided by Alexa.

00:00:27.995 --> 00:00:31.932
[grunting]

00:00:31.932 --> 00:00:33.166
[thinking] Vivillon's
Gust isn't the only thing

00:00:33.166 --> 00:00:35.068
we have to deal with.

00:00:35.068 --> 00:00:37.371
There's Surskit's Ice Beam
and Sticky Web too.

00:00:37.371 --> 00:00:39.940
How are we gonna do it?

00:00:39.940 --> 00:00:42.643
♪ I wanna be the very best ♪

00:00:42.643 --> 00:00:46.480
♪ Like no one ever was ♪

00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:49.116
♪ To catch them
is my real test ♪

00:00:49.116 --> 00:00:52.519
♪ To train them is my cause ♪

00:00:52.519 --> 00:00:55.489
♪ Pokémon gotta catch 'em all ♪
♪ It's you and me ♪

00:00:55.489 --> 00:00:58.759
♪ Pokémon ♪
♪ I know it's my destiny ♪

00:00:58.759 --> 00:01:01.562
♪ Pokémon ♪
♪ Yeah you're my best friend ♪

00:01:01.562 --> 00:01:04.598
♪ In a world we must defend ♪

00:01:04.598 --> 00:01:08.502
♪ Pokémon gotta catch 'em all ♪

00:01:08.502 --> 00:01:09.636
♪ Pokémon ♪♪

00:01:13.473 --> 00:01:14.641
ASH
"Battling On Thin Ice!"

00:01:18.645 --> 00:01:19.746
[sighs]

00:01:21.848 --> 00:01:23.684
‐ 'Ash?'
‐ Huh?

00:01:23.684 --> 00:01:25.385
‐ Here, use this.
‐ Huh? Huh!

00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:28.188
Great. Thanks.

00:01:29.456 --> 00:01:32.793
Hm. Um. Here we go.

00:01:34.828 --> 00:01:37.598
Ash, do you remember me?

00:01:37.598 --> 00:01:39.299
Huh?

00:01:40.801 --> 00:01:43.337
Think back to when you went
to camp in Pallet Town.

00:01:43.337 --> 00:01:45.772
I did too.
That's where we met.

00:01:45.772 --> 00:01:48.041
‐ At camp?
‐ That's right.

00:01:48.041 --> 00:01:50.410
We met at Professor Oak's
Pokémon Summer Camp.

00:01:50.410 --> 00:01:52.980
‐ Hey, I remember that camp.
‐ You really do?

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:56.216
Yeah, of course, I went to it.

00:01:56.216 --> 00:01:59.419
I know, and that's because
I went to that camp as well.

00:01:59.419 --> 00:02:02.723
Hm, can't say I remember you.

00:02:02.723 --> 00:02:03.991
‐ Ah!
‐ Uh?

00:02:03.991 --> 00:02:05.592
Oh, no!

00:02:06.994 --> 00:02:08.895
Sorry.

00:02:08.895 --> 00:02:11.398
[chuckles]
That's okay, Ash.

00:02:11.398 --> 00:02:13.400
'For now, you need
to concentrate on training.'

00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:15.702
‐ 'You can remember me later.'
‐ 'Right.'

00:02:15.702 --> 00:02:18.271
'I've got to say,
Pokémon battles are amazing.'

00:02:18.271 --> 00:02:20.440
You saw mine?

00:02:20.440 --> 00:02:23.477
Then you know what a totally
rotten mess I made of it.

00:02:23.477 --> 00:02:26.780
A mess? I don't think so,
you were awesome.

00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:29.182
I remember what you said
the last time we met

00:02:29.182 --> 00:02:31.652
you never give
up until the end.

00:02:31.652 --> 00:02:33.420
'You're obviously
not giving up.'

00:02:33.420 --> 00:02:35.222
'You haven't changed one bit.'

00:02:35.222 --> 00:02:37.491
[laughs]

00:02:37.491 --> 00:02:39.526
I haven't changed, have I?

00:02:39.526 --> 00:02:41.361
[laughing]

00:02:44.798 --> 00:02:46.600
I'm not giving up.

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:49.202
That just wouldn't be me
at all.

00:02:49.202 --> 00:02:50.704
'Thanks, Serena.
You're a big help.'

00:02:51.672 --> 00:02:53.306
Uh? Sure.

00:02:55.709 --> 00:02:57.911
Alexa! Can we have
another battle, please?

00:02:57.911 --> 00:02:59.379
ALEXA
Okay.

00:02:59.379 --> 00:03:01.381
PIKACHU FLETCHLING
[EXCITED]

00:03:01.381 --> 00:03:03.750
'It's not like me
to get all down on myself.'

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:05.085
I can fix all of this
by not giving up.

00:03:06.386 --> 00:03:07.554
Ready to go?

00:03:07.554 --> 00:03:08.922
[INTENT]

00:03:08.922 --> 00:03:10.223
[CHALLENGING]

00:03:10.223 --> 00:03:12.726
Noivern, use Gust!

00:03:12.726 --> 00:03:15.829
[GUST MOVE]

00:03:15.829 --> 00:03:19.132
[PAINED]/[EFFORT]

00:03:19.132 --> 00:03:22.803
Stay strong. Don't give up!
[EFFORT]

00:03:22.803 --> 00:03:24.671
Get your footing, Pikachu!

00:03:24.671 --> 00:03:26.707
And Fletchling,
keep your balance!

00:03:26.707 --> 00:03:28.542
DETERMINED]

00:03:28.542 --> 00:03:30.577
[EXERTION]

00:03:30.577 --> 00:03:32.846
Alright!
Pikachu's using its tail!

00:03:32.846 --> 00:03:35.082
Great, in that position

00:03:35.082 --> 00:03:36.917
Pikachu should be able
to keep its footing.

00:03:36.917 --> 00:03:38.418
[EFFORT]/[CONFIDENT]

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:42.222
BONNIE
Wow, look at that.

00:03:42.222 --> 00:03:43.590
Fletchling's flying
lots better now too.

00:03:43.590 --> 00:03:45.358
DEDENNE
[IMPRESSED]

00:03:45.358 --> 00:03:47.627
CLEMONT 'It's adjusting the
angle' 'of its tail feathers'

00:03:47.627 --> 00:03:49.863
'to control how
the air flows around it.'

00:03:49.863 --> 00:03:52.866
Now, Pikachu, use Thunderbolt!
And Fletchling, Razor Wind!

00:03:52.866 --> 00:03:54.201
[THUNDERBOLT MOVE]

00:03:54.201 --> 00:03:56.203
[RAZOR WIND MOVE]

00:03:56.203 --> 00:03:58.205
Alright, Noivern, dodge it!

00:03:58.205 --> 00:03:59.940
[EXERTION]

00:04:02.342 --> 00:04:04.711
[SATISFIED]

00:04:04.711 --> 00:04:08.615
Awesome! Looking good, you two.
[CONFIDENT]/[PLEASED]

00:04:08.615 --> 00:04:10.450
Looks like you're getting
the hang of it.

00:04:10.450 --> 00:04:12.853
But I'm not finished yet!
Use Gust, again!

00:04:12.853 --> 00:04:15.188
[GUST MOVE]

00:04:21.762 --> 00:04:24.531
Wow, Alexa, that was some
really helpful training.

00:04:24.531 --> 00:04:26.566
Thank you for everything.

00:04:26.566 --> 00:04:28.635
Save your thanks
until after you defeat my sister

00:04:28.635 --> 00:04:30.337
and win your first
Kalos Gym Badge.

00:04:30.337 --> 00:04:31.972
Right, I'll do my best.

00:04:31.972 --> 00:04:33.073
[DETERMINED]

00:04:33.073 --> 00:04:34.441
[EAGER]

00:04:36.443 --> 00:04:39.746
'Hmm. We've got a good defense'
against Gust now.'

00:04:39.746 --> 00:04:43.116
So that means, uh,
now you just need to figure out

00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:45.485
the ice battlefield
and Sticky Web and Psychic.

00:04:45.485 --> 00:04:47.754
I've already
figured out how to deal

00:04:47.754 --> 00:04:50.624
‐ with the ice battlefield.
‐ Yeah? What are you gonna do?

00:04:50.624 --> 00:04:52.092
'You'll find out
during the battle.'

00:04:52.092 --> 00:04:53.527
Hey, that's no fun.

00:04:56.663 --> 00:04:58.632
Well, as far as handling
Sticky Web

00:04:58.632 --> 00:04:59.966
you just leave that to me.

00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:02.636
Yes, alright,
Pikachu and Fletchling

00:05:02.636 --> 00:05:03.837
it's back to trainin'
after we eat.

00:05:03.837 --> 00:05:05.772
[SURPRISED]/[EXCITED]

00:05:13.613 --> 00:05:15.549
CLEMONT 'Allow me to help
you with your training'

00:05:15.549 --> 00:05:18.618
using the very best
of my scientific skills.

00:05:18.618 --> 00:05:21.354
Remember, the future is now,
thanks to science.

00:05:21.354 --> 00:05:23.824
And the power of technology.

00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:25.859
'Clemontic Gear, on.'

00:05:25.859 --> 00:05:28.428
'I invented this device
in anticipation'

00:05:28.428 --> 00:05:31.064
'of the very situation
Ash is now in.'

00:05:31.064 --> 00:05:34.000
I call it the Sticky Web
Sticky‐Wicket Wacker Wonk!

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.036
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

00:05:36.036 --> 00:05:38.805
Science is so amazing!

00:05:38.805 --> 00:05:41.875
I've analyzed Sticky Web's
composition at the DNA level

00:05:41.875 --> 00:05:44.711
and this device is able
to replicate its stickiness

00:05:44.711 --> 00:05:48.114
color, aroma
and nutritional value to a tee.

00:05:48.114 --> 00:05:51.384
I'm sure patent approval
is right around the corner.

00:05:51.384 --> 00:05:53.119
Well, I really don't know
what you're talking about

00:05:53.119 --> 00:05:55.088
‐ but thanks, Clemont.
‐ So, let's get started.

00:05:55.088 --> 00:05:56.823
[EXCITED]

00:05:56.823 --> 00:05:59.893
CLEMONT
'Lock on target and fire!'

00:06:01.728 --> 00:06:03.230
'Dodge it!'

00:06:03.230 --> 00:06:04.931
[EXERTION]

00:06:04.931 --> 00:06:06.333
[CONFIDENT]

00:06:06.333 --> 00:06:07.968
[CURIOUS]/[DISGUSTED]

00:06:07.968 --> 00:06:10.537
He's right!
It's the same as Sticky Web!

00:06:10.537 --> 00:06:12.239
This is what I call
training with science.

00:06:12.239 --> 00:06:14.875
Keep it up! Fire! Fire! Fire!

00:06:14.875 --> 00:06:17.010
[EXERTION]

00:06:17.010 --> 00:06:19.012
[EXERTION]

00:06:19.012 --> 00:06:20.547
Hey, you're both looking great.

00:06:20.547 --> 00:06:23.617
[EXERTION]

00:06:23.617 --> 00:06:26.753
[CHALLENGING]

00:06:26.753 --> 00:06:29.089
Not bad, but you haven't
experienced my device

00:06:29.089 --> 00:06:31.458
working at full power.

00:06:31.458 --> 00:06:33.627
Maximum level and fire!

00:06:34.761 --> 00:06:36.630
[SURPRISED]

00:06:36.630 --> 00:06:38.164
Huh, something's not right.

00:06:39.032 --> 00:06:40.867
Huh! Aah!

00:06:45.105 --> 00:06:47.374
Hm? Aah!

00:06:47.374 --> 00:06:49.442
[screaming]

